in case anybody came! (LAUGHS) And then various things from India in my paternal grandparents\rquote  house. They\rquote d picked up the usual little range of souvenirs \endash  bells, and little boxes and stuff like that. But it\rquote 
s quite striking, I think, I always meant to write an article about this, that four generations of my family \endash  my grandfather, my uncle, myself and our children \endash 
 have lived in the same part of India, and there are photographs - they were in Madras, and there were photographs of Madras. I mean, they weren\rquote 
t terribly well-informed, obviously, because they were there in the transitory - mostly because of the military - but still, in all this, it was something that was kind of there and around in the air: people moved around the globe, and that was nothing
