d come to Birmingham to study engineering. He was incredibly intelligent, and he really wanted to be a philosopher, so he introduced me to Bertrand Russell and lots of other books, and I just devoured them. And then I decided that I didn\rquote 
t really have any belief in anything. So no, I haven\rquote t had any. But I think Methodism was - I was thinking about that, actually, yesterday, when I was running, that Methodism, because it\rquote 
s a kind of religion that - well, certainly the Methodist Church that I grew up in, there was concern about social issues. For example, I remember, during Suez, so I would have been 13, and my parents and a lot of the congregation at that church signing a
