Well, thinking about my school, my grammar school \endash  King\rquote s Norton Girls\rquote  Grammar \endash  they were remarkable institutions, those Girls\rquote 
 Grammar Schools, because, particularly at that time, most of the women who were teachers there were older, and although we liked to laugh at them, and we thought they were all a bunch of old frumps, the situation probably, for man
y of them, was that they were the kind of remnants of the generation who\rquote d lost fianc\'e9
s or potential husbands in the First World War, and so most of them were unmarried. But they were very highly educated. Many of them had been to Oxbridge, or the Universi
ty of London, and teaching was really their life. And I think, particularly for students who they saw as bright and interested, they were willing to do anything really. So there were several teachers who had a very profound influence on me.
