th. That was an amazing experience, because it was so different. There were so many things that I found different, and I wanted to understand these things. And my parents had said to me, \'93Whatever you do, you must be polite. You must eat what\rquote 
s put in front of you\'94
, and all the rest of it, so when they served me what I discovered later was horsemeat, I was completely appalled, because I was very keen on horses, and I used to ride, and the idea of eating a horse was just (LAUGHS) but anyway, I dutifully ate 
