 the one who went to live in Ireland, with all the kids \endash  so he went there for a while and my brother-in-law, who is a master builder and carpenter, he was a kind of apprentice for him, and he learnt just such an 
amazing range of skills, so what he does now, after a rather chequered and long-winded story, but anyway, he\rquote s now, he buys up properties and he refurbishes them. So if you want a wall knocked down, he\rquote 
ll knock you a wall down. You want a wall built, he\rquote ll build you one. If you want a bathroom, you want a kitchen, you want a floor laid, he can do almost anything and everything, and he does. And he\rquote 
s really really good. So this is the thing he likes doing best, which is taking some horrible run-down place, and turning it into a really beautiful living space. He\rquote 
