\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12206042\charrsid12206042 Pat:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14303659\charrsid12206042 \tab 
So Brian and I were just two, and we were teaching - it was a very circumscribed curriculum, which was laid down by a committee in the University of London, books I disliked intensely. We were teaching many hours, because we had to teach evenings as well 
as daytime, and I remember saying to Brian, \'93We\rquote ve got to do something about this. We need to have a proper Anthropology Department.\'94
 And so we kind of plotted it. Then we managed to get a third person, who was Nici Nelson or Olivia Harris, I can\rquote t remember which came first. And then we went to the then Warden, Richard Hoggart, and we said, \'93
We want to be separate from Psychology\'94. \'93What? No, no, no, you\rquote re far too small\'94. But anyway, in the end, I think when there were four of us, it was agreed that we could constitute a separate Unit. We were n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15276711 ot allowed to call ourselves a \lquote Department\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14303659\charrsid12206042 
. And so I guess it was a combination of a lot of politicking and a lot of hard work, and it took off. And so the numbers grew, and always the student numbers grew faster tha
n we were able or allowed to recruit staff, but we then got another half post, and so gradually, until we got up to, I think, five or six posts, and then we finally did become a separate Department. And it stayed as a small Department for a very long time
, and then it started to grow very rapidly, and now I think there are something like 17 members of staff. And whereas the pioneers \endash  if I can call us that \endash 
 had stayed there for a very long time, the later people, there was much more turnover. I mean, people would stay several years usually, but then they\rquote d move on to something else.
