n her gap year. So we have a lot of fond memories of that place. My husband, Lionel, was working on Indian Christians. So we had a house, we ended up in the south of the city, quite close to the beach, in a new suburb of Madras, which we also got to know 
very well and became very fond of. But he worked more in Northern Madras, so he had a motor scooter, and he used to tootle off on his motor scooter \endash  when he could get it started \endash  and do his fieldwork with these Indian}{\rtlch\fcs1 
