s on my list of things that really should be done. I didn\rquote t need to editorialise his actual life history - which appears in the second chapter of the book \endash  I mean, a few things needed to be tidied up, repetit
ions and stuff, but on the whole, he started at the beginning and kind of went on to - he died last year, actually. Then I had very much hoped that it would not only make some impact in anthropology, both as a personal narrative and also particularly in e
xploring the issues around spirit possession, but that it might be read by people outside of anthropology. And I think the publishers did try a bit to kind of get the word out, and I remember the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14303659\charrsid12206042 Financial Times}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14303659\charrsid12206042  got in touch with me, which is just where you
 want to have your name mentioned! And they asked me to write a short article about the book, which I did, and that was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4084883\charrsid12206042 half-page}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14303659\charrsid12206042  in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14303659\charrsid12206042 Financial Times}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14303659\charrsid12206042 . Strange place too - yeah! But it was never really a best-seller. And I suppose, by that time, again,
 there are quite a lot of personal narratives and biographies and life histories and stuff, so it\rquote s one of a number really.
