\rquote 94, I then sat down and I wrote it, so I must have finished it over the next year, and then it went to the publisher, and it finally came out in \rquote 97, and he\rquote 
d seen it. I gave him a copy, I took a copy back when I went in 2002, and he looked at it, and he said to me, \'93The problem is\'94, he said, \'93I haven\rquote t really got anywhere to keep it\'94. Because, of course, he\rquote 
s very poor, and the rats and the damp and the white ants get into everything, so, \'93Will you look after it for me?\'94 And I said, \'93Well, I\rquote ll give you something to put it in\'94. So it wasn\rquote t that I went back with the manuscript and I
\rquote d translated it into Swahili and we went all through it line by line, not at all. It would have been - I mean, I couldn\rquote t have got away, and it would have been really difficult, and I think he\rquote 
d made the decisions, and he just used to say, \'93I trust you, and you trust me, so you do what you think is right, and that\rquote s fine by me\'94, which is very nice, but it\rquote s a heavy responsibility as well.
